         <abstract>
            <p>This paper develops an efficient algorithm which generates the pentaspherical coordinates of the spheres in an osculatory packing of the three-dimensional unit sphere. The algorithm has a tree-like structure and is easily modified so that, given a prescribed bound, it counts the number of spheres in the packing whose curvatures are less than this bound. The algorithm has been used to produce heuristic estimates of the exponent $M$ of the packing, and these indicate that $M$ is approximately 2.42.</p>
          </abstract>
